那就做這樣子

1237
01:04:11,840 --> 01:04:14,322
所以兩款遊戲都等於算是

1238
01:04:14,322 --> 01:04:16,964
一開始其實並沒有去想到要做關卡編輯這件事情

1239
01:04:16,964 --> 01:04:17,124
OK

1240
01:04:17,124 --> 01:04:18,766
You can continue

1241
01:04:18,766 --> 01:04:18,966
OK, so...

1242
01:04:18,966 --> 01:04:24,491
I'm gonna talk about this level editor thing

1243
01:04:24,491 --> 01:04:27,613
It's actually quite dangerous

1244
01:04:27,613 --> 01:04:29,915
to make a level editor

1245
01:04:29,915 --> 01:04:31,336
And this is why like...

1246
01:04:32,247 --> 01:04:36,508
what we thought at first, right? It's like making a level editor is kind of,

1247
01:04:36,508 --> 01:04:42,290
it's like, it's just a tool, right? Like Audacity or like FL Studio or, you know, Adobe. Like people

1248
01:04:42,290 --> 01:04:46,891
can just make stuff in it, they can share it, they can save files, they can open files. Like,

1249
01:04:46,891 --> 01:04:51,772
what's wrong with that? You know, it's just a tool. The problem is, it actually gets quite

1250
01:04:51,772 --> 01:04:58,254
political because if you make a level editor, if it's a normal game, it's fine, you know, people

1251
01:04:58,254 --> 01:04:58,594
just...

1252
01:04:59,408 --> 01:05:02,450
like people just make whatever levels they want.

1253
01:05:02,450 --> 01:05:07,593
No, I guess even for platform games, people can make like Nazi symbols in the level editor.

1254
01:05:07,593 --> 01:05:09,874
But that's not what I'm talking about.

1255
01:05:09,874 --> 01:05:12,376
Not here.

1256
01:05:12,376 --> 01:05:19,460
The thing is, for music game level editors, when people say like,

1257
01:05:19,460 --> 01:05:21,101
when we ask everyone, like, what do you want?

1258
01:05:21,101 --> 01:05:23,442
And they say, I want a level editor.

1259
01:05:23,442 --> 01:05:28,985
What most people are thinking of is, I want to use my favorite song in the level editor.

1260
01:05:30,560 --> 01:05:32,681
So they're not thinking, I want to make my own song and I want

1261
01:05:32,681 --> 01:05:33,501
to make a level there.

1262
01:05:33,501 --> 01:05:36,262
No, they're thinking, Oh, I really like my favorite artist song.

1263
01:05:36,262 --> 01:05:38,664
I want to make a level with that song.

1264
01:05:38,664 --> 01:05:41,545
And this is where it gets kind of dangerous.

1265
01:05:41,545 --> 01:05:51,430
Because so do you agree that sometimes tools made without

1266
01:05:51,430 --> 01:05:53,631
any instructions can be dangerous?

1267
01:05:53,631 --> 01:05:53,911
Yeah.

1268
01:05:55,217 --> 01:06:00,381
So what happened with this was that people were making songs with their favorite artists,

1269
01:06:00,381 --> 01:06:03,242
and those favorite artists, they didn't want it.

1270
01:06:03,242 --> 01:06:06,965
They didn't want their songs to be made in the level editor.

1271
01:06:06,965 --> 01:06:09,326
So there's a few approaches to this, actually.

1272
01:06:09,326 --> 01:06:15,290
So we had spent a lot of time on this because some of those artists got angry with us because

1273
01:06:15,290 --> 01:06:20,934
they say it's unethical to make a level editor when you know people are going to use

1274
01:06:20,934 --> 01:06:22,715
other artists' music in that level editor.

1275
01:06:23,557 --> 01:06:25,498
And I see their point.

1276
01:06:25,498 --> 01:06:30,783
At first, my viewpoint was that level editors are just neutral tools.

1277
01:06:30,783 --> 01:06:32,304
It's like making FL Studio.

1278
01:06:32,304 --> 01:06:36,808
Anyone can make a remix, unauthorized remix in FL Studio and share it.

1279
01:06:36,808 --> 01:06:39,230
So what's the difference with our game?

1280
01:06:39,230 --> 01:06:43,694
But I think it goes beyond that, because even though it may be legally okay,

1281
01:06:43,694 --> 01:06:45,536
morally, there's something gray there.

1282
01:06:46,471 --> 01:06:52,295
Because a lot of artists, right, how they make money is, like,

1283
01:06:52,295 --> 01:06:57,860
especially rhythm game artists, they make money by licensing

1284
01:06:57,860 --> 01:07:00,602
their tracks to other rhythm games.

1285
01:07:00,602 --> 01:07:05,986
So if there is a level editor and people use their songs

1286
01:07:05,986 --> 01:07:13,291
without us, like, buying a license for every song that every player wants to use,

1287
01:07:13,291 --> 01:07:15,753
it might, it might

1288
01:07:16,687 --> 01:07:21,228
it might be greater exclusivity off their tracks

1289
01:07:21,228 --> 01:07:25,810
because it's now more common compared to before

1290
01:07:25,810 --> 01:07:28,531
when it was only licensed to specific games.

1291
01:07:28,531 --> 01:07:30,932
So I know in the kind of artist community,

1292
01:07:30,932 --> 01:07:32,873
there's a game, do you know Osu?

1293
01:07:32,873 --> 01:07:33,513
Yeah, I know Osu.

1294
01:07:33,513 --> 01:07:34,573
There's a game called Osu.

1295
01:07:34,573 --> 01:07:35,074
Yeah, I know Osu.

1296
01:07:35,074 --> 01:07:39,115
Yeah, it's like a circle, you click the circles.

1297
01:07:39,115 --> 01:07:39,775
Yeah.

1298
01:07:39,775 --> 01:07:42,837
And that's a huge community where everything is custom,

1299
01:07:42,837 --> 01:07:44,337
everything is like custom levels,

1300
01:07:44,337 --> 01:07:45,838
everything is made for a level editor.

1301
01:07:46,318 --> 01:07:51,660
And that attracts a lot of anger from artists because, you know,

1302
01:07:51,660 --> 01:07:55,001
the developer profits from that because, you know, they sell

1303
01:07:55,001 --> 01:07:58,943
subscriptions to osu!. They sell, like, subscriptions to the leaderboard.

1304
01:07:58,943 --> 01:08:02,184
You can get supporter. They sell all the tools and stuff.

1305
01:08:02,184 --> 01:08:06,806
So indirectly, they are making money from artists' work without paying them.

1306
01:08:06,806 --> 01:08:10,327
So that's the whole gist of it.

1307
01:08:10,327 --> 01:08:12,168
So that's what we started to get into, right?

1308
01:08:12,168 --> 01:08:15,630
Because when we released the level editor, we didn't think about these things.

1309
01:08:16,043 --> 01:08:19,886
that's when it starts to feel like, oh, are we profiting from these artists?

1310
01:08:19,886 --> 01:08:23,228
Like, we have our own, we have our own levels. We have, you know, because like,

1311
01:08:23,228 --> 01:08:26,771
like that's the main game, right? We have our own levels in both games, but

1312
01:08:26,771 --> 01:08:31,854
there's a question of like, how much are we, like, how much are we benefiting from

1313
01:08:31,854 --> 01:08:37,178
these custom levels that other people are making? So we had a big talk with our team,

1314
01:08:37,178 --> 01:08:40,801
like, what do we do? Like, do we just cancel the level editor? Do we delete it?

1315
01:08:42,501 --> 01:08:49,606
Do we delete all levels that weren't made by artists who gave permission?

1316
01:08:49,606 --> 01:08:53,068
So what we did in the end was we actually thought for a long time.

1317
01:08:53,068 --> 01:08:56,151
We made something called a verified artist list.

1318
01:08:56,151 --> 01:08:57,351
So it's a website.

1319
01:08:57,351 --> 01:09:00,434
It's integrated with the game.

1320
01:09:00,434 --> 01:09:03,576
And if you type any artist in our level editor,

1321
01:09:03,576 --> 01:09:06,758
it'll first check the website, the database,

1322
01:09:06,758 --> 01:09:08,659
to see if that artist has given permission before.

1323
01:09:09,387 --> 01:09:13,670
And if they haven't given permission, then they won't let you upload it.

1324
01:09:13,670 --> 01:09:15,390
So it's a whitelist system.

1325
01:09:15,390 --> 01:09:21,554
So whitelist means that every song has been approved by the artist before they can use it.

1326
01:09:21,554 --> 01:09:23,275
So we transitioned into this system.

1327
01:09:23,275 --> 01:09:27,377
One of the problems was that we had all these old levels, right?

1328
01:09:27,377 --> 01:09:31,679
You know, the users, they spend a lot of time making these.

1329
01:09:31,679 --> 01:09:32,880
So we kind of had to decide, like...

1330
01:09:34,015 --> 01:09:39,867
Do we want to delete all of these old levels so that we can be, we can be like pure, can

1331
01:09:39,867 --> 01:09:41,451
be pure again?

1332
01:09:41,451 --> 01:09:42,212
So we did.

1333
01:09:42,212 --> 01:09:45,118
So we actually had to like, it was a hard decision, but we.

1334
01:09:46,092 --> 01:09:51,434
We had talked to the community and we said, we're going to have to disable access to all these.

1335
01:09:51,434 --> 01:09:54,815
So none of these were shared on official platforms anyway.

1336
01:09:54,815 --> 01:09:56,256
So it's shared on non-official.

1337
01:09:56,256 --> 01:10:01,918
Of course, we wouldn't share songs we don't have to license on our actual platform in the game itself.

1338
01:10:01,918 --> 01:10:04,679
So these are all on the fan discord and stuff like that.

1339
01:10:04,679 --> 01:10:08,180
But even then, even though we don't own that platform.

1340
01:10:08,761 --> 01:10:13,444
Even though we don't make many directly, there's still a moral question

1341
01:10:13,444 --> 01:10:16,686
about whether we are profiting indirectly.

1342
01:10:16,686 --> 01:10:21,149
So because of that, we decided we kind of clamped down on all

1343
01:10:21,149 --> 01:10:25,732
the old levels, and we only start approving levels once they got

1344
01:10:25,732 --> 01:10:27,353
permission from the artists.

1345
01:10:27,353 --> 01:10:28,494
And that's what we did.

1346
01:10:28,494 --> 01:10:30,095
So Yakomo, our programmer.

1347
01:10:30,746 --> 01:10:31,866
He's in Peru.

1348
01:10:31,866 --> 01:10:35,647
So he had a friend, Diego, who was good at web development.

1349
01:10:35,647 --> 01:10:39,949
So he could make a database of artists

1350
01:10:39,949 --> 01:10:41,429
who would allow their songs to be used.

1351
01:10:41,429 --> 01:10:44,390
And then we would ask everyone to,

1352
01:10:44,390 --> 01:10:47,171
we'll ask everyone to contact the artists

1353
01:10:47,171 --> 01:10:50,072
and then they have to email, they have to get a response.

1354
01:10:50,072 --> 01:10:52,553
And then they would upload the response to the website.

1355
01:10:52,553 --> 01:10:53,953
And then someone, one of our team.

1356
01:10:54,634 --> 01:10:59,598
